Building & Rebuilding
Command	Description
docker compose build	Builds images defined in your docker-compose.yml file.
docker compose build --no-cache	Builds images without using the cache.
docker compose build <service>	Builds only a specific service.
docker compose up --build	Builds images and then starts the containers. Useful if you changed your Dockerfile.
docker compose up --force-recreate	Recreates containers even if nothing changed.
docker compose up --build --force-recreate	Fully rebuilds and recreates containers.

Running Containers
Command	Description
docker compose up	Starts containers in the foreground.
docker compose up -d	Starts containers in detached mode (in the background).
docker compose start	Starts already created containers (doesnâ€™t rebuild or recreate).

Stopping & Removing Containers
Command	Description
docker compose stop	Stops running containers without removing them.
docker compose down	Stops and removes containers, networks, and default volumes.
docker compose down --volumes	Removes containers, networks, and named/anonymous volumes.
docker compose down --rmi all	Also removes all built images.
docker compose rm	Removes stopped service containers (after stop).
docker compose kill	Forcefully stops running containers.


Useful Inspection & Debugging
Command	Description
docker compose ps	Lists running services and their status.
docker compose logs	Shows logs for all services.
docker compose logs -f	Follow logs (like tail -f).
docker compose exec <service> sh	Opens a shell inside a running container.
docker compose config	Validates and shows the full resolved Compose config.
